.TH AXNODEPASS 1 "July 2026" "DigiHub" "DigiHub User Manual"
.SH NAME
axnodepass \- generate a random alphanumeric AX.25 node password
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B axnodepass
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B axnodepass
generates a fresh 6\-character random alphanumeric password, suitable for
use as an AX.25 node login password.
.PP
Unlike the APRS passcode, this password has no relationship to the
callsign; it is purely random, generated with
.I "openssl rand \-base64 12 | tr \-dc A\-Za\-z0\-9 | head \-c6"
each time it runs. DigiHub stores the value used at install time in field
18 of
.IR $HOME/.dhinfo ;
run
.BR dhedit (1)
to view, regenerate, or manually change it.
.PP
Running
.B axnodepass
directly generates and displays a new password but does not save it
anywhere; use
.B dhedit
to persist a new value into
.IR $HOME/.dhinfo .
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Generate a random AX node password:
.B axnodepass
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Password generated and printed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
The shared UI library could not be loaded.
.SH AUTHOR
Steve de Bode \- W0FFS
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR dhedit (1)
